title: Agnieszka Radwanska reaches quarterfinals of Tianjin Open
text:
Agnieszka Radwanska returns a shot against Garbine Muguruza during their women's singles semifinal match at the China Open. (Photo: Lintao Zhang, Getty Images)
CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE TIANJIN, China (AP) â€” Agnieszka Radwanska of Poland beat China's Wang Qiang 6-1, 6-1 Thursday to reach the quarterfinals of the Tianjin Open.
The second-seeded Radwanska saved all five break points she faced and won in just under an hour.
Also, Montenegro's Danka Kovinic upset sixth-seeded Teliana Pereira 6-2, 5-7, 6-1, Elizaveta Kulichkova of Russia defeated countrywoman Evgeniya Rodina 6-2, 7-5, and Tianjin native Duan Ying-Ying beat Lyudmyla Kichenok of Ukraine 6-7 (5), 6-2, 6-4.
